goals.question: What is the relationship between life expectancy and GDP per capita?

goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand if there is a correlation between a country's wealth and the life expectancy of its citizens.

goals.question: What is the trend of population growth over time?
goals.visualization: Line chart of population vs year
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand if the world population is increasing or decreasing over time.

goals.question: What is the distribution of income per person across different regions?
goals.visualization: Box plot of income per person by region
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand the income distribution across different regions and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the trend of child mortality rate over time?
goals.visualization: Line chart of child mortality rate vs year
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand if child mortality rate is decreasing over time and identify any countries that need more attention.

goals.question: What is the relationship between fertility rate and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of fertility rate vs life expectancy
goals.rationale: This visualization can help us understand if there is a correlation between a country's fertility rate and the life expectancy of its citizens.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='gdpPercap', y='lifeExp', hue='continent')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between life expectancy and GDP per capita?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('GDP per Capita')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.legend(title='Continent')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='population', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population growth over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Population Growth', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='region', y='income_per_person', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income per person across different regions?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.legend(title='Region', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='child_mortality', hue='country', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of child mortality rate over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Child Mortality Rate')
    plt.legend(title='Country', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='fertility_rate', y='life_expectancy', hue='country', legend='brief')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between fertility rate and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left', borderaxespad=0)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
